ABUJA: The National Rescue Movement (NRM) has disclosed that it opened its presidential ticket to women and youth to allow fresh air in governance come 2023. The party which is billed to elect its flag bearer for the 2023 presidential elections on June 2 in Abuja, revealed that women and youths are critical stakeholders in the Nigeria project. Chairman of the convention planning Committee, Prince Chinedu Obi said so far, nine aspirants have been screened to participate in the forthcoming primary. -Advertisement- He added that the party hopes to produce “the best candidate to rescue Nigeria from economic stagnation, political upheavals, insecurity and clueless leadership.” According to NRM, 300 delegates from across the country will take part in the primary elections. Prof. Benedicta Egbo, Mazi Okwudili Nwa-Anyaike, Barry Avotu Johnson and Sen. Ibrahim Yunusa are among the aspirants cleared to contest the presidential primary.